<br>
---------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Hey taino<br>
After reading your post i decided to throw down some of my own thoughts on aspects of your theory.<br>
<br>
&quot;It has been said that Venril Sathir and Mayong Mistmoore are not on good terms, but if they could reach common ground and unite for a common goal and eliminate mutual enemies...then why not?&quot; <br>
<br>
No way bro, lol. There is no hatred more worse than that between Mayong and Venril. I don't think they'd ever ever ally, although I know what you mean, it would benefit both parties involved. But that's just like saying Firiona and Inny should ally to kill Lanys. It just wouldn't happen.<br>
<br>
Also, I seem to be the only one who is over-emphasising Trakanon's involvment in all of this. Redemption I dont think is what he is after. Revenge is his quest. He wants nothing more than the downfull of the Ring for throwing him out and laying him to waste in the ruins of sebilis. His presence is ever more so. Just take NK for instance, the center of attraction of late. The ruined stone north of the zone which once stood tall and plain is covered in tributes to Trak, and in signs of Trak himself. Why?!? It's puzzling me no end. <br>
Ok now check this out. Ak'anon. Trak'anon.<br>
Am I the only one going &quot;wtf&quot; here? Could Ak'anon have been named after a Dragon, also exiled by the Ring of Scale, and layed to waste in the now named lands of Steamfront Mountains? What if Trak'anon and Ak'anon were exiled for the same reasons as Naggy and Vox? Although we know that wasn't the case for Trak'anon. <br>
Now enter the evil lil gnomes, who I have seen more and more of within this War than at first glance. We even have a gnome walkin around reportedly in PoH.<br>
Now correct me if im wrong but there is a Gnome on Bloodsabre faction within Ak'anon, and supposedly more. What if these gnomes once served a dragon called Ak'anon and pledged revenge on the Ring of Scale?<br>
Would explain their allegience with the Bloodsabres who are strong allys with Lanys. <br>
Now enter the Lanys/Trak relationship. <br>
An alliance there isn't such an extreme possibility, surely? Both wish to see the old world in ruins, and what if Trak would forge an alliance with Lanys? Lanys is an immortal enemy of the Ring, and so is Trak. Surely with the Malevolence Lany's would make a great ally for Trak, and we all know that Trak isn't one for being loyal, he could easily turn on Lanys himself and take the Malevolence. Trak with an almighty powerful weapon? I bet the Ring of Scale wouldn't look like such a scary opponent then. Such an allegience would also benefit Lany's. Take out the Ring, and Firiona can kiss her support goodbye, and also her aid in regaining her stolen memories from the Iksar's. And that is one crucial thing Lany's wants.<br>
And this is the most evident factor which leads me in to believing a Lany's and Trak'anon alliance is that Dorvias N'keth, the archpriest of Innoruk has discovered that Lany's finally knows where the staff part of the Malevolence, the second piece, also known as the Arm of Malevolence, is. And it has been reported that the ONLY person who could possibly know its specific location is Trak'anon himself, seen as he is the one that killed the Iksar General, Tzashk, and obtained the arm of Malevolence many years ago.<br>
<br>
This theory may seem far fetched, but whenever i think about Trak'anon's involvment, it just seems that his hatred for the Ring of Scale could lead him to alliance with probably anyone. Seen as he isn;t really a bad guy, or a good guy. Just a guy looking for revenge. <br>
<br>
<br>
Oh, one last thing, I have yet to check out Befallen. And the reports I'm hearing are VERY interesting. I suggest a number of us go and farm the zone, and identify any drops and check out the new spawns. If this is indeed, as Taino suggested, a new base of operations for Lany's than it is the strongest link we have in finding where Lany's is, and what she is up to. Besides, I want to see if the rumours are true about the new child of Hate being chained up in the basement. Could this be the person  Lany's kidnapped when she fled Neriak? All very interesting.<br>
<br>
Haloface Soulchanter<br>
55 Beguiler<br>
Defender of Highpass Hold<br>
