<br>
Trakanon was once a noble blue dragon, a trusted friend of Jalad Dar, and speculated wingmate of Phara Dar long ago. As well, he is said to be a first brood dragon, which would make him one of the direct descendants of Veeshan herself. Yet...he claims in the story of Eldril to be even older than the others. The first of her descendants perhaps? Or did he exist as an entity before ....Yet his claim may suggest he is in league with another force. One might think him some sort of possible link to The Nameless. That is...if he is gifted with prophecy as the Eldril story suggests ! Klandicar, I believe (not sure as I havn't been able to speak to him for some time) claims to be the oldest, as his time to rest in the Necropolis comes soon. I've never entirely thought the Eldril story &quot;fit&quot; so well with the way things were going. We seem to have more than one dragon claiming to be the Elder. Trakanon, in Sebilis (meaning this was after his imprisonment by the Ring for his actions against the Iksar fleet, and after the death of Jalad Dar) discussing the future with Eldril. It may be he has maintained his &quot;nobility&quot; then, or he was quite mad, and at the time merely considered himself a prophet, and ancient in the sense he claims. <br>
<br>
Now, were he a prophet, and able to see things that would come to pass. It's safe to say there has been a reason for his actions that went against those dragonkin he was most  &quot;loyal&quot; to. Perhaps exile was a small price to pay, to ensure certain events were or were not allowed to take place. It may very well be that Trakenon went against the wishes of the Ring of Scale to assault the Iksar fleet those years ago because had the fleet not been stopped....something unfortunate would have happened. Wether in Trakanon's eyes (it's not yet clear when he lost his &quot;nobility&quot;) or Norrath as a whole.  As well, it could very well be that Trakanon knew even then the importance of the Talisman kept by Rile.  <br>
<br>
Incredible speculation , that I thought to share. It would rely on the story of Eldril being &quot;legit&quot;, and would mean that the story line taking place currently has been in the works for some time. Trakanon did wish for the Iksar to be stopped, and whispered among the Ring of Scale they were a threat. Even then, long ago....did he know of the Talisman ? What else did Trakanon see.....?<br>
<br>
Now he may wish revenge on the Ring for making him an outcast, but we're not yet clear on the facts behind it all. Is Trakenon wise, and blessed with foresight? Or his he manipulative and treacherous?<br>
